[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":666},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2021\u002F05\u002F12\u002Fvscode-settings-i-recommend-for-developers\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2021\u002F05\u002F12\u002Fvscode-settings-i-recommend-for-developers\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2021\u002F05\u002F12\u002Fvscode-settings-i-recommend-for-developers\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2021\u002F05\u002F12\u002Fvscode-settings-i-recommend-for-developers\u002F":642,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2021\u002F05\u002F12\u002Fvscode-settings-i-recommend-for-developers\u002F":651},"\u002Fvscode\u002F20210512\u002F2779926364\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":622,"date":623,"description":624,"extension":625,"lang":626,"meta":627,"navigation":628,"path":629,"readingMinutes":630,"seo":631,"standalone":632,"stem":633,"tags":634,"tldr":638,"updated":639,"url":640,"__hash__":641},"content\u002Fen\u002FVSCode\u002Fvscode-settings-i-recommend-for-developers.md","VSCode Settings I Recommend for Developers","3443400390",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":612},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,27,34,42,47,54,57,60,66,70,73,76,110,117,123,133,140,146,150,157,162,168,172,179,185,200,205,208,279,283,301,306,310,317,322,326,336,608],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"A sharper tool means better work. As someone who's lived in VSCode for years, knowing your editor settings genuinely makes dev work smoother — easier to navigate, easier to debug. So here's a writeup of the VSCode settings I find handy.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"show-whitespace-and-tab-characters","Show whitespace and tab characters",[17,25,26],{},"By default in VSCode, you don't really see those tiny white dots (representing spaces and tabs). What do they look like?",[17,28,29],{},[30,31],"img",{"alt":32,"src":33},"Whitespace dots","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FVSCode\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202021-05-12%2009.04.24.png",[17,35,36,37,41],{},"The setting is called ",[38,39,40],"code",{},"renderControlCharacters",". Open VSCode settings and search for it.",[17,43,44],{},[30,45],{"alt":40,"src":46},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FVSCode\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202021-05-12%2009.08.57.png",[17,48,49,50,53],{},"I'd also recommend changing ",[38,51,52],{},"renderWhitespace"," to All, which makes both spaces and tab characters visible.",[17,55,56],{},"This is genuinely important for real-world dev — you absolutely want to know whether you're using spaces or tabs at a glance.",[17,58,59],{},"Quick reminder: a small dot means a space, and an arrow means a tab.",[17,61,62],{},[30,63],{"alt":64,"src":65},"Dots vs arrows","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FVSCode\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202021-05-12%2010.04.44.png",[12,67,69],{"id":68},"default-end-of-line-character","Default end-of-line character",[17,71,72],{},"If you're a frontend dev using ESLint, this one is essential.",[17,74,75],{},"By default, files might use CRLF line endings — common on Windows. But most style guides (including ESLint) recommend LF. To fix this, add this to your settings:",[77,78,83],"pre",{"className":79,"code":80,"language":81,"meta":82,"style":82},"language-json shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","\"files.eol\": \"\\n\",\n","json","",[38,84,85],{"__ignoreMap":82},[86,87,90,94,98,101,105,107],"span",{"class":88,"line":89},"line",1,[86,91,93],{"class":92},"sTRMh","\"files.eol\"",[86,95,97],{"class":96},"sMAXC",": ",[86,99,100],{"class":92},"\"",[86,102,104],{"class":103},"sWyjQ","\\n",[86,106,100],{"class":92},[86,108,109],{"class":96},",\n",[17,111,112,113,116],{},"Or just search for ",[38,114,115],{},"eol"," in settings.",[17,118,119],{},[30,120],{"alt":121,"src":122},"eol setting","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FVSCode\u002F202105120915.png",[17,124,125,126,128,129,132],{},"This is the default end-of-line character — ",[38,127,104],{}," means LF, ",[38,130,131],{},"\\r\\n"," means CRLF. The reason to standardise: CRLF indentation can occasionally cause visible formatting issues when files move across OSes, so most style guides recommend LF (CRLF only really exists for Windows).",[17,134,135,136,139],{},"Side note: you can also tweak tab size. If you want a tab to render as a specific number of spaces, search for ",[38,137,138],{},"tabSize",".",[17,141,142],{},[30,143],{"alt":144,"src":145},"editor.tabSize","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FVSCode\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202021-05-12%2009.35.48.png",[12,147,149],{"id":148},"editor-font-size","Editor font size",[17,151,152,153,156],{},"Sometimes the default font is too small. Search for ",[38,154,155],{},"terminal.integrated.fontSize"," to change the terminal font size.",[17,158,159],{},[30,160],{"alt":155,"src":161},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FVSCode\u002F202105120918.png",[17,163,164,165,139],{},"For the editor font size, use ",[38,166,167],{},"editor.fontSize",[12,169,171],{"id":170},"emmet","Emmet",[17,173,174,175,178],{},"Emmet is on by default, but sometimes the setting gets reset. Search for ",[38,176,177],{},"triggerExpansionOnTab"," and make sure it's checked.",[17,180,181],{},[30,182],{"alt":183,"src":184},"Emmet trigger","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FVSCode\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202021-05-12%2009.23.20.png",[17,186,187,188,191,192,195,196,199],{},"Emmet only expands in certain file types by default — so things like ",[38,189,190],{},".ejs"," and ",[38,193,194],{},".vue"," won't work out of the box. Search for ",[38,197,198],{},"includeLanguages"," and add them:",[17,201,202],{},[30,203],{"alt":198,"src":204},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FVSCode\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202021-05-12%2009.25.54.png",[17,206,207],{},"Quick copy-paste version:",[77,209,211],{"className":79,"code":210,"language":81,"meta":82,"style":82},"\"emmet.includeLanguages\": {\n  \"javascript\": \"javascriptreact\",\n  \"vue-html\": \"html\",\n  \"plaintext\": \"jade\",\n  \"ejs\": \"html\",\n},\n",[38,212,213,221,235,248,261,273],{"__ignoreMap":82},[86,214,215,218],{"class":88,"line":89},[86,216,217],{"class":92},"\"emmet.includeLanguages\"",[86,219,220],{"class":96},": {\n",[86,222,224,228,230,233],{"class":88,"line":223},2,[86,225,227],{"class":226},"sKpQp","  \"javascript\"",[86,229,97],{"class":96},[86,231,232],{"class":92},"\"javascriptreact\"",[86,234,109],{"class":96},[86,236,238,241,243,246],{"class":88,"line":237},3,[86,239,240],{"class":226},"  \"vue-html\"",[86,242,97],{"class":96},[86,244,245],{"class":92},"\"html\"",[86,247,109],{"class":96},[86,249,251,254,256,259],{"class":88,"line":250},4,[86,252,253],{"class":226},"  \"plaintext\"",[86,255,97],{"class":96},[86,257,258],{"class":92},"\"jade\"",[86,260,109],{"class":96},[86,262,264,267,269,271],{"class":88,"line":263},5,[86,265,266],{"class":226},"  \"ejs\"",[86,268,97],{"class":96},[86,270,245],{"class":92},[86,272,109],{"class":96},[86,274,276],{"class":88,"line":275},6,[86,277,278],{"class":96},"},\n",[12,280,282],{"id":281},"emmet-defaults","Emmet defaults",[17,284,285,286,289,290,191,293,296,297,300],{},"VSCode also lets you customise Emmet's HTML template defaults. Every time you ",[38,287,288],{},"!+tab"," you might end up tweaking ",[38,291,292],{},"lang",[38,294,295],{},"charset"," — but you can just set the defaults once. Search for ",[38,298,299],{},"emmet.variables"," and set the values you want.",[17,302,303],{},[30,304],{"alt":299,"src":305},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FVSCode\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202021-05-12%2009.31.33.png",[12,307,309],{"id":308},"mouse-wheel-zoom","Mouse wheel zoom",[17,311,312,313,316],{},"Another useful one. Normally to zoom in\u002Fout you press some key combo. VSCode lets you zoom by Ctrl + scroll wheel — just search for ",[38,314,315],{},"mouseWheelZoom"," and check it.",[17,318,319],{},[30,320],{"alt":315,"src":321},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FVSCode\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202021-05-12%2009.28.39.png",[12,323,325],{"id":324},"lazy-copy-paste-json","Lazy copy-paste JSON",[17,327,328,329,332,333,335],{},"Here's the full bundle from above — just paste into ",[38,330,331],{},"settings.json",". If you already customised your own ",[38,334,331],{},", I'd suggest backing it up first and adding properties one at a time.",[77,337,339],{"className":79,"code":338,"language":81,"meta":82,"style":82},"{\n    \u002F\u002F Emmet tab expansion\n    \"emmet.triggerExpansionOnTab\": true,\n    \u002F\u002F Enable Emmet for additional languages\n    \"emmet.includeLanguages\": {\n        \"javascript\": \"javascriptreact\",\n        \"vue-html\": \"html\",\n        \"plaintext\": \"jade\",\n        \"ejs\": \"html\",\n    },\n    \u002F\u002F Show whitespace characters\n    \"editor.renderWhitespace\": \"all\",\n    \"editor.renderControlCharacters\": true,\n    \u002F\u002F Default HTML template variables\n    \"emmet.variables\": {\n        \"lang\": \"en\",\n        \"charset\": \"UTF-8\",\n    },\n    \u002F\u002F Default tab size (spaces)\n    \"editor.tabSize\": 2,\n    \u002F\u002F Default end-of-line character. \\n is LF, \\r\\n is CRLF.\n    \"files.eol\": \"\\n\",\n    \u002F\u002F Editor font size\n    \"editor.fontSize\": 16,\n    \u002F\u002F Terminal font size\n    \"terminal.integrated.fontSize\": 16,\n    \u002F\u002F Ctrl + scroll to zoom\n    \"editor.mouseWheelZoom\": true,\n}\n",[38,340,341,346,352,365,370,377,388,400,412,424,430,436,449,461,467,475,488,501,506,512,525,531,547,553,566,572,584,590,602],{"__ignoreMap":82},[86,342,343],{"class":88,"line":89},[86,344,345],{"class":96},"{\n",[86,347,348],{"class":88,"line":223},[86,349,351],{"class":350},"sQrFR","    \u002F\u002F Emmet tab expansion\n",[86,353,354,357,359,363],{"class":88,"line":237},[86,355,356],{"class":226},"    \"emmet.triggerExpansionOnTab\"",[86,358,97],{"class":96},[86,360,362],{"class":361},"sCcAr","true",[86,364,109],{"class":96},[86,366,367],{"class":88,"line":250},[86,368,369],{"class":350},"    \u002F\u002F Enable Emmet for additional languages\n",[86,371,372,375],{"class":88,"line":263},[86,373,374],{"class":226},"    \"emmet.includeLanguages\"",[86,376,220],{"class":96},[86,378,379,382,384,386],{"class":88,"line":275},[86,380,381],{"class":226},"        \"javascript\"",[86,383,97],{"class":96},[86,385,232],{"class":92},[86,387,109],{"class":96},[86,389,391,394,396,398],{"class":88,"line":390},7,[86,392,393],{"class":226},"        \"vue-html\"",[86,395,97],{"class":96},[86,397,245],{"class":92},[86,399,109],{"class":96},[86,401,403,406,408,410],{"class":88,"line":402},8,[86,404,405],{"class":226},"        \"plaintext\"",[86,407,97],{"class":96},[86,409,258],{"class":92},[86,411,109],{"class":96},[86,413,415,418,420,422],{"class":88,"line":414},9,[86,416,417],{"class":226},"        \"ejs\"",[86,419,97],{"class":96},[86,421,245],{"class":92},[86,423,109],{"class":96},[86,425,427],{"class":88,"line":426},10,[86,428,429],{"class":96},"    },\n",[86,431,433],{"class":88,"line":432},11,[86,434,435],{"class":350},"    \u002F\u002F Show whitespace characters\n",[86,437,439,442,444,447],{"class":88,"line":438},12,[86,440,441],{"class":226},"    \"editor.renderWhitespace\"",[86,443,97],{"class":96},[86,445,446],{"class":92},"\"all\"",[86,448,109],{"class":96},[86,450,452,455,457,459],{"class":88,"line":451},13,[86,453,454],{"class":226},"    \"editor.renderControlCharacters\"",[86,456,97],{"class":96},[86,458,362],{"class":361},[86,460,109],{"class":96},[86,462,464],{"class":88,"line":463},14,[86,465,466],{"class":350},"    \u002F\u002F Default HTML template variables\n",[86,468,470,473],{"class":88,"line":469},15,[86,471,472],{"class":226},"    \"emmet.variables\"",[86,474,220],{"class":96},[86,476,478,481,483,486],{"class":88,"line":477},16,[86,479,480],{"class":226},"        \"lang\"",[86,482,97],{"class":96},[86,484,485],{"class":92},"\"en\"",[86,487,109],{"class":96},[86,489,491,494,496,499],{"class":88,"line":490},17,[86,492,493],{"class":226},"        \"charset\"",[86,495,97],{"class":96},[86,497,498],{"class":92},"\"UTF-8\"",[86,500,109],{"class":96},[86,502,504],{"class":88,"line":503},18,[86,505,429],{"class":96},[86,507,509],{"class":88,"line":508},19,[86,510,511],{"class":350},"    \u002F\u002F Default tab size (spaces)\n",[86,513,515,518,520,523],{"class":88,"line":514},20,[86,516,517],{"class":226},"    \"editor.tabSize\"",[86,519,97],{"class":96},[86,521,522],{"class":361},"2",[86,524,109],{"class":96},[86,526,528],{"class":88,"line":527},21,[86,529,530],{"class":350},"    \u002F\u002F Default end-of-line character. \\n is LF, \\r\\n is CRLF.\n",[86,532,534,537,539,541,543,545],{"class":88,"line":533},22,[86,535,536],{"class":226},"    \"files.eol\"",[86,538,97],{"class":96},[86,540,100],{"class":92},[86,542,104],{"class":103},[86,544,100],{"class":92},[86,546,109],{"class":96},[86,548,550],{"class":88,"line":549},23,[86,551,552],{"class":350},"    \u002F\u002F Editor font size\n",[86,554,556,559,561,564],{"class":88,"line":555},24,[86,557,558],{"class":226},"    \"editor.fontSize\"",[86,560,97],{"class":96},[86,562,563],{"class":361},"16",[86,565,109],{"class":96},[86,567,569],{"class":88,"line":568},25,[86,570,571],{"class":350},"    \u002F\u002F Terminal font size\n",[86,573,575,578,580,582],{"class":88,"line":574},26,[86,576,577],{"class":226},"    \"terminal.integrated.fontSize\"",[86,579,97],{"class":96},[86,581,563],{"class":361},[86,583,109],{"class":96},[86,585,587],{"class":88,"line":586},27,[86,588,589],{"class":350},"    \u002F\u002F Ctrl + scroll to zoom\n",[86,591,593,596,598,600],{"class":88,"line":592},28,[86,594,595],{"class":226},"    \"editor.mouseWheelZoom\"",[86,597,97],{"class":96},[86,599,362],{"class":361},[86,601,109],{"class":96},[86,603,605],{"class":88,"line":604},29,[86,606,607],{"class":96},"}\n",[609,610,611],"style",{},"html pre.shiki code .sTRMh, html code.shiki .sTRMh{--shiki-default:#ADDCFF}html pre.shiki code .sMAXC, html code.shiki .sMAXC{--shiki-default:#F0F3F6}html pre.shiki code .sWyjQ, html code.shiki .sWyjQ{--shiki-default:#FF9492}html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html pre.shiki code .sKpQp, html code.shiki .sKpQp{--shiki-default:#72F088}html pre.shiki code .sQrFR, html code.shiki .sQrFR{--shiki-default:#BDC4CC}html pre.shiki code .sCcAr, html code.shiki .sCcAr{--shiki-default:#91CBFF}",{"title":82,"searchDepth":223,"depth":223,"links":613},[614,615,616,617,618,619,620,621],{"id":14,"depth":223,"text":15},{"id":22,"depth":223,"text":23},{"id":68,"depth":223,"text":69},{"id":148,"depth":223,"text":149},{"id":170,"depth":223,"text":171},{"id":281,"depth":223,"text":282},{"id":308,"depth":223,"text":309},{"id":324,"depth":223,"text":325},"VSCode","2021-05-12 09:02:38","A sharper tool means better work. After spending years in VSCode, I've put together the settings that make day-to-day dev work smoother — covering whitespace rendering, line endings, fonts, Emmet, and more.","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002Fvscode-settings-i-recommend-for-developers","3",{"title":6,"description":624},false,"en\u002FVSCode\u002Fvscode-settings-i-recommend-for-developers",[622,635,636,637],"Settings","Setting","Development",null,"2023-04-16 20:01:00","\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2021\u002F05\u002F12\u002Fvscode-settings-i-recommend-for-developers\u002F","LACWhxtG4WGaKnUZATxz5VXO0S7dekAlxjiInJhtdBY",{"newer":643,"older":647},{"url":644,"title":645,"date":646},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2021\u002F05\u002F16\u002Fgithub-pages-build-failure-jekyll-conflict-fix\u002F","GitHub Pages \"Build Failure\" — the .nojekyll Fix for Hexo and Static Sites","2021-05-16 21:00:47",{"url":648,"title":649,"date":650},"\u002Fen\u002Fgit\u002F2021\u002F05\u002F07\u002Fgithub-private-email-gh007-fix\u002F","git push Error GH007: Your push would publish a private email address.","2021-05-07 11:35:23",[652,657,662],{"url":653,"title":654,"date":655,"readingMinutes":656},"\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2025\u002F04\u002F24\u002Fvscode-cannot-find-git-set-git-path\u002F","VSCode 'Can't Find Git, Install It or Use git.path' — How to Fix","2025-04-24 09:52:23","1",{"url":658,"title":659,"date":660,"readingMinutes":661},"\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2024\u002F09\u002F08\u002Fgithub-copilot-tips-and-tricks-deep-dive\u002F","GitHub Copilot Feels Awkward? You Might Just Not Know These Tricks","2024-09-08 13:06:00","5",{"url":663,"title":664,"date":665,"readingMinutes":656},"\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2023\u002F10\u002F26\u002Fvscode-vue-custom-component-syntax-highlight-fix\u002F","Vue Custom Components Lost Their Highlighting in VSCode — Here's the Fix","2023-10-26 11:03:07",1784010293128]